title: regression 1.46 -> 1.47 big-endian backtrace-related UI tests failing

labels.name: A-runtime
labels.description: Area: std's runtime and "pre-main" init for handling backtraces, unwinds, stack overflows

labels.name: T-libs-api
labels.description: Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

labels.name: T-libs
labels.description: Relevant to the library team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
~~~~
test [ui] ui/backtrace-debuginfo.rs ... FAILED
test [ui] ui/backtrace.rs ... FAILED
test [ui] ui/std-backtrace.rs ... FAILED
~~~~

- OK on 1.46: [s390x](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=s390x&ver=1.46.0%2Bdfsg1-1&stamp=1598726465&raw=0) | [ppc64](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=ppc64&ver=1.46.0%2Bdfsg1-1&stamp=1598724366&raw=0)
- fails on 1.47: [s390x](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=s390x&ver=1.47.0%7Ebeta.2%2Bdfsg1-1%7Eexp1&stamp=1599833893&raw=0) | [powerpc](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=powerpc&ver=1.47.0%7Ebeta.2%2Bdfsg1-1%7Eexp1&stamp=1599873502&raw=0) | [ppc64](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=ppc64&ver=1.47.0%7Ebeta.2%2Bdfsg1-1%7Eexp1&stamp=1599860160&raw=0) | [sparc64](https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=rustc&arch=sparc64&ver=1.47.0%7Ebeta.2%2Bdfsg1-1%7Eexp1&stamp=1599827178&raw=0)

In all cases, we are using gdb 9.2 and LLVM 10.

The tests themselves haven't changed since ~1.38, so it must be an actual behavioural change in rustc.
